<description><![CDATA[<h2>&nbsp;Conditional operators</h2><p><br></p><p>Generally the program execution starts with the first block and then the subsequent blocks. </p><p><br></p><p>This order can be modified by Conditional execution block IF. </p><p><br></p><p>A logical expression is evaluated and the block is executed only if the result is True. </p><p><br></p><p>We put an&nbsp;<strong>IF&nbsp;</strong>condition inside a&nbsp;<strong>Repeat loop Block</strong>&nbsp;to print 'Small' when the loop index is less than 2. Else it prints 'Big'.</p><p><br></p><h2>Procedure </h2><p><br></p><ol><li>select the&nbsp;<strong>if-do block</strong>&nbsp;from the&nbsp;<strong>In/Out</strong>&nbsp;section.</li><li>Press the Gear button on the If-do block. </li><li>A popup box showing else and else if will appear.</li><li>Drag the else from the left side&nbsp;and fix it below the if on the right side. </li><li>Click the Gear button again to close the popup.</li></ol><p><br></p><p>We use the comparison operator to evaluate the If condition.</p>]]></description></xml>